Saudi King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud delivers his closing remarks at the G20 summit in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, on Nov. 22, 2020. The Group of 20 (G20) Saudi Arabia's Presidency said on Sunday the G20 Riyadh Summit reaffirmed the spirit of cooperation, which has always been the cornerstone of the G20 successes. (G20 Saudi Arabia/Handout via Xinhua)The Group of 20 (G20) Saudi Arabia's Presidency said on Sunday the G20 Riyadh Summit reaffirmed the spirit of cooperation, which has always been the cornerstone of the G20 successes.Saudi King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud stressed in his closing remarks at the annual G20 summit that cooperation is necessary today more than ever to face the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic and to build a prosperous future for the people of the world.King Salman noted that G20 has achieved a lot this year. G20 nations have upheld the commitment to continuing to work together to rise to the challenge of the pandemic in order to safeguard lives and livelihoods and protect the most vulnerable groups, he said.

